The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Sunday, March 27, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 A fine hattrick by Somnath Shaw earned Sporting Union a 3-1 victory over Jagrihi in their BHA league first division group B match at the Mohammedan Sporting ground Saturday. 

 Shaw hit home a minute from the start before adding another in the 27th minute. Jagrihi?s Asit Patra reduced the margin in the 30th minute, but Shaw banged the final nail in with another strike in the 48th minute.

 Coal India Sports Promotion Board, in association with the Office Sports Federation, will organise an inter-office prize money double wicket meet at the Kalighat ground from Monday. 

 Top office teams like FCI, United Bank, SBI, CESC, Metro Railway, Central Excise, Reserve Bank, WBSEB, AG Bengal, Postal SB, Coal India will take part, according to a press release issued here Saturday.

 FOOTBALL: National League ?Mohun Bagan vs Dempo (Salt Lake), 3.15pm.




